I have evaluated the current state of the Gemini Collaboration Bridge and identified that while the core MCP-to-Discord functionality is complete and functional, the system lacks a persistence layer for long-term state management and multi-tenant scalability. 

I have updated the following architectural specifications:
- **`specs/04-EPICS.md`**: Added **Epic 7: Persistence & State Management** to track the transition from PM2-only state to a dedicated SQLite-based store.
- **`specs/03-ARCHITECTURE.md`**: Defined the proposed **Persistence Layer** schema (Projects, Spaces, Audit logs) and its responsibilities.
- **`specs/context-map.md`**: Added the planned `src/core/state-store.ts` module to the feature map.

This evolution will allow GCB to support multi-provider mappings (e.g., a project linked to both Discord and Slack), user-specific command history, and more robust recovery after system restarts.

[SUMMARY]: Defined the architecture for a new Persistence Layer (Epic 7) and updated specifications.
